<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="49" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d49">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">702.60D11/165</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Finnish Minister</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Procopé</hi></persName>)<note n="66" xml:id="d49fn66">This note was acknowledged with “very sincere
                                gratitude” by the Minister on March 9, 1942.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-07">March 7,
                                1942</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: In view of the statement
                            in your note of March 4, 1942<note n="67" xml:id="d49fn67">Not printed;
                                this was a personal letter from the Minister to Mr. Welles.</note>
                            that Finnish citizens in American service in Finland are not subjected
                            to other restrictions than other Finnish citizens, I am prepared to
                            agree to withdraw the limitations imposed upon American citizens in
                            Finnish employ in this country set forth in the Department’s note of
                            January 27, 1942.</p>
                        <p>I hope this will ease your situation.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sumner Welles</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>